    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        -2.5,
        0.0,
        2.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "message": "THE KHORGAUL ROOST\n\nA burned-out hilltop hold. Charred furniture. Wind through broken stone. Some things are still warm to the touch — though no fire has been laid here for years.\n\nThe Drawing-In started somewhere. It might have started here."
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        2.5,
        0.0,
        2.5
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "message": "Scorched stone marker:\n\n'The Roost burned in a season nobody wrote down. The wind takes the ash a little further every year. By the time you read this it may already be gone.'"
    },
    {
      "type": "sign",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        -2.0
      ],
      "rotation_y": 0.0,
      "message": "Charred floorboards. A handful of black feathers in a corner. The smell is faint but familiar — old smoke, and something underneath it that doesn't have a clean name."
    },
    {
      "type": "npc",
      "pos": [
        0.0,
        0.0,
        1.0
      ],
      "rotation_y": 3.141592653589793,
      "name": "Cultist Drev",
      "body_color": [
        0.32,
        0.28,
        0.3,
        1.0
      ],
      "hat_color": [
        0.55,
        0.42,
        0.32,
        1.0
      ],
      "idle_hint": "[E] Speak with the cultist",
      "dialog_tree": {
        "start": "root",
        "nodes": {
          "root": {
            "speaker": "Cultist Drev",
            "text": "*he is sweeping ash, slowly. The broom is older than he is. He looks up with the friendliness of a man who has not had visitors in a long while.*\n\nWelcome, friend. Welcome to the Roost. The Master is away on long business — but he'll be back, oh yes. He'll be back any day now.",
            "choices": [
              {"label": "How long ago did the Roost burn?", "next": "burn"},
              {"label": "When did you last see your master?", "next": "last"},
              {"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}
            ]
          },
          "burn": {
            "speaker": "Cultist Drev",
            "text": "Burn? *he looks confused.*\n\nThere was — there was a season of bad lightning, perhaps. The roof needs work. The Master will see to it when he returns.\n\n*the wind moves a piece of burnt cloth across the floor. He doesn't seem to notice it.*",
            "choices": [
              {"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}
            ]
          },
          "last": {
            "speaker": "Cultist Drev",
            "text": "Last? Oh, not long. Not long at all. I keep his rooms in order. He'll be back in the next breath, or the breath after, or the one after that.\n\nWalker — would you like a cup of something? I have... I had... let me see what we have.\n\n*he doesn't move.*",
            "choices": [
              {"label": "Walk well.", "next": "bye"}
            ]
          },
          "bye": {
            "speaker": "Cultist Drev",
            "text": "Walk well. Tell the Master, if you see him on the road, that the Roost is kept. The Roost is kept."
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ],
